    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>PayPal Praise and Problems</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Sue Spang letter says PayPal, online payment system discussed in June 29 article, has not been helpful to her in dealing with fraudulent account set up in her name with a stolen credit card number</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>I received a letter from PayPal (by regular mail) thanking me for using its service and offering to increase the amount in my account.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>I received a letter from PayPal (by regular mail) thanking me for using its service and offering to increase the amount in my account.</p>
        <p>Unfortunately, I had never set up an account with PayPal. Someone was able to use my name and credit card number. I have had little luck with PayPal's fraud or customer service departments and have had to cancel my credit card and notify all credit bureaus. I don't know if the culprit will ever be caught.  SUE SPANG  Lexington, S.C.</p>
      </block>
    </body.content>
